---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About — QA Learning"
  description="About QA Learning: a personal QA study portfolio built and maintained by bykplx1. Learn about the site's intent, content review process, and how to contribute."
>
  <main id="main" class="about-page">
    <article class="prose about-prose">
      <span class="eyebrow">about this site</span>
      <h1>About QA Learning</h1>

      <h2>What this site is</h2>
      <p>
        QA Learning is a personal portfolio and study site for software quality assurance. It covers
        QA fundamentals across six curriculum tracks — from testing foundations through to AI/LLM
        quality engineering — with written lessons, practice quizzes, a mock exam, and a set of
        self-directed project briefs.
      </p>
      <p>
        The site is built and maintained by
        <a href="https://github.com/bykplx1" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">bykplx1</a>
        as a learning portfolio. It is not affiliated with any certification body or employer.
      </p>

      <h2>Content review process</h2>
      <p>
        All 36 curriculum topics are hand-written MDX, versioned in
        <a href="https://github.com/bykplx1/qa-learning-site" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">the public repository</a>.
        The review process is straightforward:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Content is drafted against established QA references (ISTQB syllabi, practitioner literature).</li>
        <li>Quiz questions are written to be unambiguous, with a single correct answer and a plain-English explanation.</li>
        <li>Factual corrections and improvements are accepted via GitHub issues or pull requests.</li>
        <li>There is no formal editorial board — this is a solo portfolio project. Treat the content as a study aid, not a definitive authority.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Tech stack</h2>
      <p>
        Built with Astro 6, MDX, React 19, Tailwind v4, Drizzle ORM, and Neon Postgres. Hosted on
        Vercel. Open-source under the
        <a href="https://github.com/bykplx1/qa-learning-site/blob/main/LICENSE" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">MIT licence</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact &amp; corrections</h2>
      <p>
        For content corrections, feature ideas, or questions, open a
        <a href="https://github.com/bykplx1/qa-learning-site/issues" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">GitHub issue</a>
        or email
        <a href="mailto:byk.plai@gmail.com">byk.plai@gmail.com</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        For privacy-related requests (data deletion, questions about stored data) see the
        <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>.
      </p>
    </article>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about-page {
    max-width: 760px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 48px 40px 64px;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .about-page {
      padding: 32px 20px 48px;
    }
  }

  .about-prose h1 {
    margin: 8px 0 4px;
  }
</style>
